\b0\fs34 \
\

\fs40 1 cup granulated sugar, plus more for rolling cookies.\
3/4 cup butter, at room temperature\
1 egg\
3 tbsp. molasses\
2 cups flour, sifted\
1 tsp. baking soda\
1 1/2 tsp. ground ginger\
1 tsp. cinnamon\
1/2 tsp. each salt, ground cloves, and freshly grated nutmeg\
1 cup powdered sugar\
1 tsp. lemon juice\
\
Preheat oven to 350 degrees.  In a large bowl, cream 1 cup granulated sugar\
with butter until light and fluffy, about 3 minutes.\
Mix in egg and molasses.\
In a medium bowl, stir together flour, baking soda, and spices.  Add to butter \
mixture and blend well.\
Fill a shallow bowl with granulated sugar.  Break off walnut-size pieces of dough and roll into balls.  Roll balls in sugar.\
Arrange on greased cookies sheets and bake until golden  brown, about \
10 minutes.  Transfer to cooling racks.\
Meanwhile, make glaze: Combine powered sugar with 1 tsp. water and stir \
until smooth, then stir in Lemon juice.\
Drizzle glaze over cookies.  \
